results.name: a(n) is the largest number such that all of a(n)'s length-n substrings are distinct and divisible by 99.
example: a(4) is 9900990 because its length-4 substrings 9900, 9009, 0099, 0990) are all distinct and divisible by 99 and there is no larger number with this property
results.author: _Hans Havermann_, Mar 29 2004
